Patient: What kind of food can I eat to help with my heart failure?

Healthcare Educator: You should eat fresh fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and lean proteins. Avoid high sodium and unhealthy fats.

Patient: But I love traditional African-American food. Are there any heart-healthy options?

Healthcare Educator: Absolutely! You can prepare healthier versions of traditional foods, like using lean meats or low-sodium seasonings.

Patient: What about exercise? I don't feel safe exercising outside in my neighborhood.

Healthcare Educator: You can try safe indoor exercises, like yoga or indoor cycling. It's important to stay active.

Patient: Will changing my diet and exercise routine really help my heart?

Healthcare Educator: Yes, a heart-healthy diet and regular exercise can greatly improve your heart health. You'll feel better overall too!
